    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_433008">This might be a good time to remind fellow Rogues of the likelihood that Poison will get revamped, and that they should add input to the 3 main threads that carry the discussion.<br />
 <br />
<a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/eq/showthread.php?t=30538" target="_blank">EQTraders</a><br />
 <br />
<a href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/eq/showthread.php?t=29921" target="_blank">Turlo's Post</a><br />
 <br />
<a href="http://forums.station.sony.com/eq/posts/list.m?topic_id=49517" target="_blank">EQLive</a><br />
 <br />
 <br />
Other than basic mechanics of making poisons and applying them, there have been two distinct issues in providing feedback to Ngreth:<br />
 <br />
1. Rogues fall into 2 camps about how much net DPS should be gained. This is a SIGNIFICANT problem. Personally I think net DPS gain should be minimal.<br />
2. There has been a lot of apathy concerning feedback. If you care, get involved in the discussion.<br />
 <br />
IMO poisons could add a lot of variety to certain rogues daily activities if they are well thought out in design and implementation. Let us make game wide useful poisons of a general nature (equivalent to current available effects - snare, slow, debuff, add to resists, cures) that can be used by anyone making the Rogue Tradeskill viable. Additionally let us make poisons which help rogues solo (split, stun, mezz, snare, slow etc).</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
