    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_433296">I agree, no DPS increase is necessary. IMO Poisons should be <br />
<br />
1) Usable by everyone (like Alchemy potions), but I think they should have to purchase a &quot;Use Poison&quot; skill first.<br />
2) Some poisons should work like a self-buff (not periodic, occasional procs), or this effect could be for rogues (with special AAs, or maybe without) only.<br />
3) Be designed to add soloability for rogues; standard effects like snare, stun, mez, self-heal, split, fear, etc.<br />
4) be designed to add utility; perhaps some special rogue-only unique effects, like increase Evade speed or chance. Bristlebane special (rogue-only)poisons could change the target model randomly when it goes off , or change target to look like a group member, or randomly shadow step the rogue (thus shedding aggro like an Evade). <img src="images/smilies/emote_smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smile" class="inlineimg" /><br />
5) ability to have multiple (perhaps 1 per weapon?) poisons active at once.<br />
<br />
Purpose should be to add variety, distinction, group utility, and perhaps soloability....not more DPS.<br />
<br />
Thanks for considering an upgrade.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
