    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_433344">There should be 2 major categories of poison;<br />
<br />
Damage (Direct Damage, Damage over time, etc)<br />
<br />
Utility (Snare, Debuffs, aggro reduction, Etc)<br />
<br />
The DPS boost should be significant enough to make it useful. The current boost to dps is laughable. If they are not going to make the dps hit useful, then they should stop now and just not even bother with the revamp.<br />
<br />
Things like aggro reduction would be a huge benefit as well, I know sometimes my dps is simply too high for the group I am in, and in this instance a dps boost would be useless but something to lower aggro would be nice. That said, we need both or it is not worth it. There are times where more dps is good and times where it is not good.<br />
<br />
Mez and crap like that we already have Disciplines for.<br />
<br />
I disagree with everyone being able to use poison's. I have been poisoning since the early UO days and I am utterly against anyone except rogues having the apply poison skill. How about we do it like UO did in giving rogues the ability to apply poison buffs to other classes. This makes us more valuable to the group, give us the ability to make money off the skill, and makes effects available to others without giving our skill away. Everyone wins.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
