    <div align="left" id="post_message_433354"><div align="center" style="margin:5px; margin-top:5px; ">
<table width="85%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="#333333" class="bbcodeQUOTE">
  
  <tr>
    <td colspan="3" align="center" valign="middle">
	
	<div align="left"><b><div align="left" style="font-size: 12px; color: #999999; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong>Feochadan said:</strong></div></b></div></td>
 
	</tr>
  <tr>   
    <td width="30" align="center" valign="middle"><img src="/forums/images/openq.gif" width="30" height="30" ></td>
    <td>
		<div align="left" style="font-size: 12px; color: #999999; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Please, don't touch this. Poisons are useless like they are, and it's better that they stay so, instead of having to farm for days and pay thousands of pps for some barely useful effect.<br />
Rogues have better to do with poison from AAs/discs like Envenomed Blades than with any tradeskill.<br />
And btw, the type 3 aug with an improvement to the reuse time of Docent of Toxicity is only made to be laughed at (and to laugh at the designer who did this).</div>
		</td>
    <td width="30" align="center" valign="middle"><img src="/forums/images/closeq.gif" width="30" height="30" align="right"></td>
  </tr>
</table>
</div>As it is poisons need to be revamped if we want to have a real benefit of them. Where I understand you do not want to have to farm (I don't either, there are already many quests / tradeskills requiring that) many rogues have waited for this revamp.<br />
<br />
Our dps is not and should not be poison dependent.<br />
I like our utility poisons (I really only use the snare) better. <br />
I think the duration of the poison should be up'd (15 min is too short).<br />
We could see added variety to the utility poisons.<br />
I am not hopin to see poisons be able to stack (execpt maybe if we good a nice 1 charge opener for example stack it with an utility one, but I really find the 1 charge poisons uninteresting).<br />
It would be nice to have simplified recipes allowing more combinations. Some poisons have a double effect such as hate reduce + str debuff, could add interest to give poisons 2 effects and we decide wich combination is most wanted for a given situation, all effects being dependent on a specific component as long as not 2 dmg effects could be made.<br />
<br />
Poison should be tuned to the current content, and current content should also drop some components. Having to go back to PoP and GoD to farm components is annoying and many of us don't even bother... poisons are not good enough for wasting that much time.<br />
We should be able to work on our poisons as we are grouping for our character's progression that being xp or quests or keys.<br />
There are also nice ideas on the thread linked above about poisons for AAs or duration extensions.<br />
The poison quests GM, mortar, trophy etc... were long and tedious. Getting to GM poison crafter with max trophy, master sketch took a lot of work. There should be a real benefit from all that. <br />
<br />
Poisons should remain rogue only useable.<br />
<br />
I would like to see a poison helping with endurance (there are lifetaps, there are mana and hp regen buffs and potions but nothing besides Third wind and resting helps our endurance). It is a bit far fetched and would be nice to have an actual buff doing that but a poison helping in that field is an alternative.<br />
I fairly new to the rogue class (lvl 80 but only 350 AAs not maxed on endurance regen), not in a high end guild and I suffer a lot of lacking endurance regen.<br />
I would like to be able to use Razor / Swiftblade on every mob (provided I stayed hidden enough) and dps named on raids for example but at this time I cannot. I hope AAs will help and finishing my cultural set too, but I run out of endurance on any raid I join due to the raid timer for rest experience unless I only use my discs on named and not at all on trash.<br />
In groups I can keep Razor up np but not swiftblade, that would drain too much endurance unless it is a slower pace group.</div>
