    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_433521">In order for poisons to be viable at all, we need a few things:<br />
<br />
1)  Poisons that have variety - ie poisons that increase hate, decrease hate, snare, debuff, slow, etc.  They offer some utility for just the user.  These poisons should be tradable, but have a short duration - 10-20 mins.<br />
<br />
2)  Poisons that a rogue can use/make that increases our group/raid utility.  This is going to be more on the line of the Shaman Puma/Panther buffs.  We should be able to create a poison that only we can apply which will effect the entire group.  This would be a 15 min &quot;Panther-like&quot; buff which would proc a DD, hate reducer, aggro increaser, etc.  Have the recast on these poisons 15 mins so on raids we don't get shuffled from group to group just to &quot;apply&quot; these poisons.<br />
<br />
3)  Poisons need to have common/easy to obtain reagents.  This has been a HUGE issue for WAY too long.  Maybe have 4 tiers of poisons - the ones made with reagents vendor bought only last 5 mins, the ones that use vendor bought reagents plus the Master Sketch last 10 mins, the ones made with farmed reagents last 15 mins and finally the ones made with farmed reagents plus the Master Sketch last 20 mins.<br />
<br />
Just a few ideas.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
