    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_433537">Just my 2 cents:<br />
<br />
What about a new line of rogue utility poisons where the ingredients are challenging to get (although possible with a group or solo), but the finished results don't have charges?  A poison &quot;clicky&quot; buff, if you will.  <br />
<br />
Either self-only or able to be applied to others, enhanced (possibly) with AA (give me a LITTLE credit for earning PM3, haha).<br />
<br />
A rogue willing to farm the ingredients/finish the line of quests/etc would have essentially a bag of utility poisons that never run out...perhaps:<br />
<br />
SNARE<br />
SLOW (30-50pct maybe, nothing to make the chanters/shamans/beastlords worry)<br />
ROOT<br />
AGGRO REDUCTION (or even a +hate poison for situations where we find ourselves tanking)<br />
MEZ OR PACIFY (maybe a small radius aoe pacify, short duration)<br />
DD PROC (or a line of different ones: fire, cold, disease, poison, magic-based)<br />
DEBUFFS (AC, ATK, resists...very small and stackable, so 1 or 2 rogues in a group wouldn't have a huge difference, but a dozen or so proccing -5 or 10 MR would make a dent on a raid)<br />
<br />
...nothing that would compete with a dedicated class with these abilities (don't want to put anyone out of business, and I don't want to see rogues become a third rate slower/puller/etc), just something to add to our utility somewhat.  Maybe add levels similar to the Rk I-III spells, so the raiders get a bit of a bump, but the casual players willing to work a bit can stay competitive.  Possibly make them only fire on a successful backstab, in the case of the pacify/mez.<br />
<br />
Perhaps make them extremely short duration and stackable; that is, have them last one or two ticks, so their duration would depend on repeated procing.  For example, a rogue could stack a slow poison with an aggro reduction poison, so the mob would (mostly) stay slowed, but the repeated slow landing would be counteracted by the aggro reducer.  A highly resistant mob would be hard to slow, as it is for the dedicated slowing classes.<br />
<br />
Another idea would be a short duration group buff proc (I'm thinking song window)...either a DD, lifetap, etc.<br />
<br />
Let's face it, many of these abilities we already have (or have had) with items like the locustlure or the serrated bone dirk or the ornate pants, which many of us still carry around, despite their being terribly obsolete, just for the effect.<br />
<br />
I'm thinking of something along the lines of an epic quest (fairly long and involved, but nothing that requires a raid or high end group to get), that results in something along the lines of a bandolier with the rogue version of the ranger's Endless Quiver AA and a handful of utility poisons that we can use when needed.<br />
<br />
Let's face it, many of us put a LOT of work into building the make poison skill, and other than a brief period of time when OoW came out (with the augments), we've really had very little use for it.  Almost 10 years later, I don't expect to get rich, have no desire to be the slower in a pick up group, and can't imagine soloing regularly for experience.  However, it would be nice, in a pinch, to have SOME purpose other than dps, which comes and goes (relatively) with every expansion.<br />
<br />
Dave<br />
<br />
Another thought:  To make poisons scale with the new expansions, just have the new poisons consist of the old poison + components from the new expansion?  I.E.  TBS poison + drop(s) from SoF = SoF poison.<br />
<br />
Last throught:  A request...please, PLEASE don't &quot;dumb down&quot; the poison making skill.  Many of us invested a TON of time and effort to build a skill that had very little, if any, use for nearly a decade.  To see a bunch of twinked alts with vendor or bazaar bought GM status a month after the revamp would kill me.</div>
