    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_433538">Here are a few suggestions for some types of poisons that I think would be potentially useful.<br />
<br />
1. A poison that procs something like a nullify magic effect on the mob to remove his buffs that don't have poison, disease, curse or corruption counters.  This would be useful while soloing because it could remove a mob's haste, damage shield, run speed, armor class and hit point buffs.  It could also perhaps be useful in certain types of groups.<br />
<br />
2. A poison that applies a &quot;reverse damage shield&quot; to the mob so it would damage itself every time it hit anybody.  It would also overwrite the mob's own damage shield which would be <b><i>hugely</i></b> beneficial on some mobs.  Think in terms of the cleric spell Mark of Retribution.  (I <i><u>think</u></i> that's the one.  Those &quot;Mark of xxx&quot; spells are a mystery to me.)</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
