    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_433544">I would just like to request that if you don't like poisons you explain why instead of making childish comments about how crap the system is or how rubbish SOE is.<br />
 <br />
For those people talking about DPS improvements, I think the following is safe to assume: if the DPS is significant, then ALL rogues will be expected to utilize poisons, ALL events will be balanced around that additional DPS in the future and ALL gained DPS will result in lack of AA's, Discs and Weapons so that rogues remain balanced with other DPS classes.<br />
 <br />
I would rather see poisons having mixed effects with a rule of thumb that the cast time is either instant or very close to instant when they are applied. If a poison requires a rogue to calculate dot/dd damage versus loss of regular DPS during cast time, it is too complicated and will not scale from low level players to end game players. Instead, poisons should carry some risk/reward alternatives e.g. I might lose DPS, but the mob is debuffed; I might lose DPS but the proc has a chance to cast slow, which means I might not have to bando a slow weapon; I might lose DPS but .......<br />
 <br />
I would like to see poisons tradeable.<br />
 <br />
I would like some novel use poisons that improve desirability of rogues in groups, again with a risk reward structure; A 40% slow aura; Poison DS etc<br />
 <br />
I see a huge opportunity to use rogue poisons to assist rogues in soloing for decent experience.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
