    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_433547">I would not just gut the charged poisons of the GM assassin seal, I don't know about you but I worked damn hard on that years ago. How about they just revamp it where either charged bottles Stack, or flag the charged coffin bottle as combinable in a coffin bottle to create up to a 100 charge bottle. Those are two perfectly viable idea's that give us more poisons without throwing the system away. A little tweaking and what we have currently is just fine.<br />
<br />
Any suggestion that results in loss of DPS = a bad suggestion. We are a dps class, if you want to do something else. Play another class. Utility is good, but not at the expense of losing dps, at a minimum all utility should be viable without the rogue sacrificing their standard dps.<br />
<br />
Additionally, they need to make poison's applicable by slot. This whole buff nonsense is really one of the major hindrances to the poison system. I should be able to apply poison to my main hand, my off hand, or even my ranged and see their timer in the Aura window or temp buff window. Same should apply if they give us the ability to apply poison to others.<br />
<br />
WoW has a good example here, they have a trade window slot for applying buffs to items. Something similar to that would work extremely well.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
