    <div align="left" id="post_message_433572"><div align="center" style="margin:5px; margin-top:5px; ">
<table width="85%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="#333333" class="bbcodeQUOTE">
  
  <tr>
    <td colspan="3" align="center" valign="middle">
	
	<div align="left"><b><div align="left" style="font-size: 12px; color: #999999; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong>Ngreth Thergn said:</strong></div></b></div></td>
 
	</tr>
  <tr>   
    <td width="30" align="center" valign="middle"><img src="/forums/images/openq.gif" width="30" height="30" ></td>
    <td>
		<div align="left" style="font-size: 12px; color: #999999; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Well..<br />
You can also.  Make poisons in the field and hand it to the person.  I just do not feel it needs to be bound to an &quot;apply poison&quot; skill.  Yes I see how they can buy them and bring them with them, and not &quot;need&quot; you, but really.  I don't see rogues as &quot;not needed&quot; any more than any other DPS class.</div>
		</td>
    <td width="30" align="center" valign="middle"><img src="/forums/images/closeq.gif" width="30" height="30" align="right"></td>
  </tr>
</table>
</div>You have to look at the state of the game as it is currently. People go to their groups already stocked, there is very little &quot;Manufacturing on the fly&quot;.<br />
<br />
I do not view rogues as a &quot;Not needed&quot; class, I simply see no reason to give any other class our abilities. I have no objections to making our poisons more available to other classes via using us. I simply object to the notion of other classes getting our skills and as such a bunch of Rogue twinks power leveled up to get poison and be poison bots. That will end up happening if poisons can be applied by anyone, just like there are a plethora of Alchemy bots. Short term view is it looks neat on paper, but ends up falling flat on its face in a short while.<br />
<br />
Concerning drops, I fail to see the rare drops thing either. I have more bags just packed with &quot;Rare&quot; poison ingredients then I want to admit too. Easily 65% of my entire bank space is absorbed by them.<br />
<br />
On that note, it would be nice if we could get poison ingredients stacked to 100 more universally.<br />
<br />
Granted I am likely wasting my breath here and you guys are going to do it how you please. I really think the &quot;apply poison&quot; skill should be used again, I think throwing it out the window is a waste. Granted those off us who have actually been around long enough to really care are an extreme minority, but that is how I think.<br />
<br />
The Ability for us to Apply poison to others weapons, and potentially proc buffs and debuffs in a group/raid setting would be a Huge boon to the poison system. Selling poisons on the bazaar is just a huge boon to a few rogue bots grinding out poisons for money. It is like the difference between a Cheeseburger and a steak, Both are good. Clearly one is better. Speaking of raid, it would be Exceptionally useful if the utility buffs &quot;If any&quot; affect players via radius or via raid. This way it is not limited to just the group.<br />
<br />
Also as another note, consider this. If rogues are the ones capable of applying poisons only, then that also opens up the path for you guys to give us some meaningful AA surrounding poisons. More AA = More grinding = More time played = More money for SoE.</div>
