    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_433604">There's something else I would like to suggest, Ngreth, which I think has been mentioned before by others.  I gather that it's not really something that is entirely within your normal range of work, but I'd like to throw it out for discussion and consideration anyway since we are talking about poisons in general here.<br />
<br />
The potions in the game now can be used from the &quot;potion belt window.&quot;  I'd love to see a similar way to use poisons without having to open my packs and move one out to a general inventory slot to click it, and without using any of my current precious potion belt slots.  I'm thinking that one of several solutions could work.<br />
<br />
1. Make the poisons &quot;potion belt usable&quot; and give rogues an expanded &quot;potion belt window&quot; with at least 1 or 2 additional potion slots available right away and a few more we could accumulate with AAs or tasks.<br />
<br />
2. Make the poisons usable in a new &quot;<i><b>poison</b></i> belt window&quot; which would be similar to the &quot;potion belt window&quot; but which would only work with poisons.<br />
<br />
3. Add a few specialized &quot;poison specific slots&quot; to the &quot;potion belt window&quot; which would only show up for characters who were rogues, and have the ability to open more of these slots through AAs or tasks.<br />
<br />
The reason I would want more slots is that potions are so useful now that I already carry a significant variety of them, more than I can actually fit in the 4 potion belt slots I currently have open.  I would really hate to have to bump out some of those potions to devote some of my 4 potion slots to poisons.<br />
<br />
I'd love to see your thoughts on this as well as feedback from other rogues.</div>
