    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_433611">We have a lot of utility in the &quot;old world&quot; poisons (slows &amp; snares), but the fact they take up one inventory slot each (ie they don't stack) really makes them almost worthless except for very rare special circumstances. It'd be great to make them stackable , but still needing to take one out of stack and click to use (eg like gate potions). Ideally some of the rarer ones ought to produce more than 1 dose too otherwise you'd spend 100x longer farming components than actually using them, once again relegating them to obscurity.<br />
<br />
As for utility in groups and raids. I don't want to be a buffing class and it doesn't fit in with the role play, but I see poisons as viable utility via debuffs. That may even include small improvements to raid dps by reducing weaknesses. Eg acid to soften up the armour a bit or weakening their resistances to spells (eg scratching madness, although -10 only is a bit miserly given the effort required to be able to make that poison).<br />
<br />
I don't really think these should be significant DPS boosts to rogues themselves as our DPS is already given through more mainstream needs. I certainly wouldn't want to get in the situation where people take into account our poisons DPS when trying to balance the class. Hence why I think poison DPS, if any, should be via debuffs helping everyone rather than only the rogue applying it.<br />
<br />
I completely agree regarding adding lifetap poisons. I'm not sure how it really fits in with roleplaying, but rogues are hands down the worst solo class by miles. Given the lack of low players this *is* a major issue as right now it takes some serious dedication for people to level up new rogues - that or having someone who can powerlevel you (which shouldn't really be an assumption).</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
