</div>I know about that and indeed I use that for PoP era poisons, but it doesn't work on any of the older poisons. Making all those old poisons work in the coffin bottle would be good, but tbh for one-shot poisons unlike the duration buff PoP style ones a case could be made for the initial combine granting 10-dose poisons to start with. Being able to combine 10x 10-dose potions to get 100 dose ones would be superbly handy. Inventory management is one of the biggest blocks to using poisons right now.<br />
<br />
As for other classes using poisons, sorry I disagree. We do already have sellable items (augments) and maybe we could sell poisons to other rogues too, but I view this as rogue utility. It's lessened somewhat if everyone gets it. I'd like our poisons to benefit the group, but for the group to require the rogue to get that benefit.<br />
<br />
Look at the stink raised by clarity potions and chanters grumbling (rightly so). Imagine if shaman could make and sell ultra-reliable slow-proc buff potions or there were complete-heal potions with a 10 sec reuse timer. Other classes would also start grumbling. So I don't really see the need to take our pretty minimal utility and make it buyable in the bazaar.<br />
<br />
Brog</div>
