</div>Poisons have already been used to make armor augments, and in the future could easily be used to make them again. They could also expand them to make weapon augments that add damage or procs. In the past they had limited control of rare drops - and I believe today they have far better control so that something like this would not be overpowering.<br />
 <br />
In terms of guidance on the overall effect - tbh I think it is unnecessary. The effect of existing poisons is already in game and has a clear delineation between poison effects and alchemy effects. Slows, dots, debuffs, DD's, hate reducers, snares, roots mezzes all exist, many are just broken for one reason or another. If rogues today had access to all of these effects as intended in a working system, our ability to offer more utility to groups and solo and offer a little more utility on raids would not be in question.</div>
