    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_433816">Selling poisons to everyone, just No. God I can't believe anyone would even support that.<br />
<br />
You want to make major profits from pressing the combine button, fine pickup a tradeskill. Poisoning is going to always be minimal profits. Here is the thing even Utility would have very little impact as Alchemy potions cover most of the bases already. At most we would bring bottled snare to the table (Oh whoopee, there is an AA for that).<br />
<br />
Here is the system as I feel would work into everyone's favor, including those wanting to make money off it.<br />
<br />
The Two types of poison I mentioned earlier Utility and DPS.<br />
<br />
AA - Poison Application: 1 Rank, This gives you the ability to Apply poison to Another players weapon slot.<br />
AA - Poison Application Mastery: Each rank increases the Duration of poison applied to weapons by x%.  (Think of this AA as the Rogue equal to Spell buff duration)<br />
AA - Rogues Miasmic Aura: Gives rogues an Aura that enhances the effectiveness of poison effects on all members in a radius.<br />
AA - Miasmic Aura Mastery: Each rank enhances the potency of poison effects on all members in a radius. (Think of this as an Aura form of Docent of Toxicity. Much like our trap AA which is worthless, it will not be as powerful as directly casting Tox, but with ranks it will come close. I would think since we have no aura and most really want utility this would really be a huge thing to alot of rogues)<br />
<br />
<br />
What the first two AA do is satiate both groups; those of us who do not want to see our poison's on the bazaar, and those of us who want to use poisoning to make a profit. If a rogue has invested some AA and can drop a 2 hour poison buff on someone, people would pay for that IF the effects prove worthwhile.<br />
<br />
The last two AA are geared right at our group utility to further enhance the poison revamp.<br />
<br />
Point is we already have the poisons we need, they simply need to Scale up with the levels, have easier to obtain ingredients, higher stack values, and be applicable to others. The AA are suggestions to enhance that which is clear that we need.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
<br>
<table width="100%%"  border="0" cellpadding="3">
