    <div align="left" id="post_message_433843">Yea, honest to god the Trap AA should be just flat removed and refunded to any rogue who invested in it.<br />
<br />
Everyone gets this impression I am against change, as you can see I am not. This old rogue can learn new tricks. I am just very particular and want the new tricks to be worth my time investment, not something that is going to waste mine and everyone elses time. If my class is to be a &quot;One Trick Pony&quot;, (Which I do not believe we are, although our options are rather limited) Then by god I want that one trick to be Fantastic. <img src="images/smilies/emote_pimp.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Pimp" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
I just hope Ngreth's lack of continued participation in this thread does not mean he is not continuing to read it. His's idea's as presented were not bad, they just were not going to do anything to improve the system over the duration. A little revision and out of the box thinking shows that he can change the system into something that not only is an immediate boost to all rogues willing to use it, but is a Boost to all players and gives Sony more options for long term rogue enhancement and viability. That is not to say my idea is the perfect final solution, far from it. I am just trying to stop the &quot;Revamp&quot; from being another Dead end path that once you hit the end you are done.</div>
